ccre.chan

Interface FloatInput

  • All Superinterfaces:
    FloatInputPoll, FloatInputProducer
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FloatTuner
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFloatTuner, CompoundFloatTuner, FloatStatus

    public interface FloatInput
extends FloatInputPoll, FloatInputProducer
    A FloatInput is a way to get the current state of a float input, and to subscribe to notifications of changes in the float input's value. FloatInput is the combination of FloatInputPoll and FloatInputProducer. By convention, most float inputs and outputs have states that range from -1.0f to 1.0f.
    See Also:
    FloatInputPoll, FloatInputProducer
